title: 'Disappointing durability'
body: The sole is soft and great, and the grip is good too. I didn't find anything special about it, but was happy with the comfort. But within 3 months, the material of the straps started wearing off, and by the 4th month, the strap came off. At this price point, the chappals are a huge disappointment.

title: 'Product satisfies all the needs it was bought for.'
body: I have been seeing Solethreads adverts. I was keen to try, however not confident on brands that are pushed through Instagram or FB. Had poor experience with Neeman.  Bought this one in Sale during Prime Day. I really liked what they have made and delivered.  The Chappal fits well. It's scientific design hugs the feet well. While walking it cushions your weight. Grip works fine, I have tested it in rains. In all, a good product to trust.
